Section 1:
1 L.D. 1097
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
4 STATE OF MAINE
5 SENATE
6 132ND LEGISLATURE
7 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
8 SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 719, L.D. 1097, “An Act to Provide De-
9 escalation and Behavior Intervention Training for School Personnel”
10 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
11 'Resolve, to Require the Department of Education to Convene a Group to Develop
12 Best Practices for De-escalation and Behavior Intervention'
13 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
14 'Sec. 1. Convening of group to develop best practices. Resolved: That the
15 Department of Education shall convene teachers and other educators and experts in de-
16 escalation and behavior intervention to develop best practices for training in the following
17 topics:
18 1. Positive behavior interventions;
19 2. Communicative intent of behaviors;
20 3. Alternatives to restrictive procedures, including techniques to identify events and
21 environmental factors that may escalate behavior;
22 4. De-escalation methods;
23 5. Standards for using restraint and seclusion procedures;
24 6. Obtaining emergency medical assistance;
25 7. The physiological and psychological effect of restraint and seclusion;
26 8. Monitoring and responding to a child's physical signs of distress;
27 9. The timely reporting and documenting of each incident involving the dangerous
28 behavior of a student and the law governing dangerous behavior prevention and
29 intervention under the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 20-A, section 6555; and
30 10. Positive behavior strategies.
31 The department shall distribute the best practices for training in de-escalation and
32 behavior intervention to all school administrative units in the State no later than September
33 1, 2026.'
Page 1 - 132LR1266(04)
SENATE AMENDMENT
SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 719, L.D. 1097
1 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
2 number to read consecutively.
3 SUMMARY
44 This amendment replaces the bill with a resolve. The amendment removes the
55 requirement in the bill that all school administrative units provide training in de-escalation
66 and behavior intervention to each of its administrators, teachers and education technicians.
77 The amendment retains the requirement in the bill that the Department of Education
88 convene a group of teachers and experts in de-escalation and behavior intervention to
99 develop best practices for training to be distributed to all school administrative units.
1100 SPONSORED BY: ___________________________________
1111 (Senator ROTUNDO, M.)
1122 COUNTY: Androscoggin
